content: {'id': '0103b164-d785-32c4-a027-093b898711b5', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India antitrust watchdog clears JSW Paints' bid for up to 75% stake in Akzo Nobel India", 'description': '', 'summary': "India's antitrust body said on Tuesday it has cleared JSW Paints' deal to acquire up to 75% stake in Dutch paint maker Akzo Nobel's Indian unit. content: {'id': '73e4d9ce-6835-32da-a9e5-b58949eb05c9', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': 'Asian Paints aims to quash Indian antitrust probe, saying investigation order mishandled', 'description': '', 'summary': "NEW DELHI (Reuters) -India's biggest paints maker, Asian Paints, is seeking to quash an antitrust inquiry, arguing that officials damaged its reputation by publishing – and then deleting – allegations against its CEO from the investigation order, legal papers show. content: {'id': '75133417-5109-38c6-83d0-9d41a9978b61', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "Birla's paints unit files antitrust case against India's Asian Paints, sources say", 'description': '', 'summary': "NEW DELHI (Reuters) -Aditya Birla Group's Indian paints venture has filed an antitrust complaint against market leader Asian Paints for allegedly abusing its market position, three sources said, a case that could lead to a stand off between the two industry rivals.  Asian Paints is India's biggest player with a 52% market share, but it has lost some of its dominance after Birla Opus launched in February 2024 and grew rapidly to garner a near 7% market share by March this year, Elara Capital data shows.  The Competition Commission of India (CCI) has in recent weeks been reviewing a confidential complaint filed by Birla Opus alleging abuse of its position by Asian Paints, said the two sources, who declined to be named as the discussions are private.", 'pubDate': '2025-06-06T10:52:14Z', 'displayTime': '2025-06-06T10:52:14Z', 'isHosted': True, 'bypassModal': False, 'previewUrl': None, 'thumbnail': {'originalUrl': 'https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/48fbe3312120339c4dd173e94b898e73', 'originalWidth': 800, 'originalHeight': 563, 'caption': 'An employee of a paint shop operates an Asian Paints colour mixture machine inside a paint shop in Ahmedabad', 'resolutions': [{'url': 'https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/knEXrhxZw.5p6rFu3XPBIA--~B/aD01NjM7dz04MDA7YXBwaWQ9eXRhY2h5b24-/https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/48fbe3312120339c4dd173e94b898e73', 'width': 800, 'height': 563, 'tag': 'original'}, {'url': 'https://s.yimg.com/uu/api/res/1.2/XgrT0VIU3QPRdPOXetRlWQ--~B/Zmk9c3RyaW07aD0xMjg7dz0xNzA7YXBwaWQ9eXRhY2h5b24-/https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/48fbe3312120339c4dd173e94b898e73', 'width': 170, 'height': 128, 'tag': '170x128'}]}, 'provider': {'displayName': 'Reuters', 'url': 'https://www.reuters.com/'}, 'canonicalUrl': {'url': 'https://sg.finance.yahoo.com/news/birlas-paints-unit-files-antitrust-105214755.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'SG', 'lang': 'en-SG'}, 'clickThroughUrl': {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/birlas-paints-unit-files-antitrust-105214755.html', 'site': 'finance', 'region': 'US', 'lang': 'en-US'}, 'metadata': {'editorsPick': False}, 'finance': {'premiumFinance': {'isPremiumNews': False, 'isPremiumFreeNews': False}}, 'storyline': None}
